                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Your April 8, 4 p.m. Department approves presentation of memorandum
                    transmitted with your despatch of April 5, and presentation of memorandum as
                    outlined in your telegram, except <pb facs="1144" n="1024" xml:id="pg_1024"/>
                    for last paragraph of concluding portion. It desires that this paragraph should
                    read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The compliance with this patriotic duty, the incorporation into the
                            budget for 1921–23 [<hi rend="italic">1922–23?</hi>] of the necessary
                            reforms, the congressional approval of that budget before June 30th
                            next, would be heralded by my government as a real demonstration in this
                            field of successful republican government in Cuba. The failure to give
                            that demonstration under so clear a necessity would be fatal to the
                            possibility of averting imminent financial disaster to the Cuban
                            Treasury, and could not but be regarded by my Government with the
                            gravest concern.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
